							<body  ><div class="section"><p class="VoteReason">A party vote was called for on the question<em>,</em> <em>That the Social Security (Extension of Young Persons Services and Re</em><em>medial Matters) Amendment Bill</em><em> be now read a third time.</em></p><p class="VoteCount"><strong>Ayes 61</strong></p><p class="VoteText">New Zealand National 59; ACT New Zealand 1; United Future 1.</p><p class="VoteCount"><strong>Noes 60</strong></p><p class="VoteText">New Zealand Labour 32; Green Party 14; New Zealand First 12; Māori Party 2.</p><p class="VoteResult">Bill read a third time.</p><p class="CentredEndingItalics">Sitting suspended from 6:01 p.m. to 7.30 p.m.</p></div></body>
